---
alwaysApply: true
---

Write self-explanatory code.

- Do NOT write docstrings by default.
- Add a docstring/comment ONLY if behavior is non-obvious, tricky, or surprising.
- Never explain what is already clear from names and types.
- Keep docstrings short (1–4 lines), focus on "why", not "what".
- Prefer clear naming and small functions over documentation.
- Do not produce large documentation blocks unless explicitly asked.